related_questions.question: Do all Delta employees fly for free?
related_questions.snippet: Delta Airline employees, their families and guests can fly for a reduced rate or free, using a Delta Buddy Pass. However, they must fly standby, meaning they are not guaranteed seats. Travel is subject to the availability of space at departure time. Buddy Passes cannot be used for business, according to Delta Airlines.

related_questions.question: How do I become a Delta flight attendant?
related_questions.snippet: Applicants must have a high school degree or GED, the ability to work in the U.S., English fluency and be at least 21 years of age by Jan. 1, 2020. Flight attendants must be willing to fly both international and domestic routes, and have a flexible schedule, since Delta flights operate day and night, year-round.Aug 26, 2019
